ğŸ¯ Challenge Overview

The password for the next level is stored in a hidden file inside the inhere directory.
Hidden files in Linux start with a dot (.) and are not shown using a normal ls command.

ğŸ§  Key Idea

To view hidden files, the ls command must be used with specific options.
Once the hidden file is identified, its contents can be read to obtain the password.

ğŸ§­ Method Used

* Navigate into the inhere directory

* List all files including hidden ones

* Read the hidden file containing the password

ğŸ’» Commands Executed
ls
cd inhere
ls -alph
cat -- ...Hiding-From-You

ğŸ” Password Retrieved
2WmrDFRmJIg3IPxneAaMGhap0pFhF3NJ

ğŸ“˜ Command Explanation

* ls
Lists visible files in the current directory.

* cd inhere
Moves into the directory where the password file is stored.

* ls -alph
Displays all files, including hidden files, in a detailed and readable format.

*cat -- ...Hiding-From-You
Reads the hidden file.
The -- ensures the filename is treated correctly even with special characters.
